      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A constant buzzing sound from your AC unit could indeed be the capacitor, which is responsible for starting the motor and regulating its speed. If the capacitor is failing, it can cause the motor to hum or buzz without spinning. However, capacitors can be dangerous to handle, as they store an electrical charge. It's not recommended to attempt fixing this yourself. A professional technician can safely replace the capacitor and ensure your AC unit is functioning properly. Remember, it's always better to leave electrical repairs to the experts to avoid any potential hazards.",
